'''BeetleCam'''是一種安置起來用以近距離拍攝野生動物的遙控相機，裝有[[DSLR|DSLR]]。<ref>{{cite web |author = Priya Ganapati, Wired |title = Robotic Buggy Takes Stunning Photos of African Wildlife |date = April 19, 2010 |url = http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2010/04/robotic-buggy-takes-stunning-photos-of-african-wildlife/ |accessdate = 2013-09-19 |archive-date = 2013-09-21 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130921111943/http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2010/04/robotic-buggy-takes-stunning-photos-of-african-wildlife/ |dead-url = no }}</ref> 其發明人是威爾·布拉德·盧卡斯（Will Burrard-Lucas）和他的兄弟馬特（Matt），首次亮相于2010年的“BeetleCam探險”（The Adventures of BeetleCam）電視劇中。<ref>{{cite web |author = Will Burrard-Lucas |title = The Adventures of BeetleCam |date = April 19, 2010 |url = http://blog.burrard-lucas.com/2010/04/adventures-of-beetlecam/ |accessdate = 2013-09-19 |archive-date = 2012-03-09 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120309174207/http://blog.burrard-lucas.com/2010/04/adventures-of-beetlecam/ |dead-url = no }}</ref> 當時用來拍攝坦桑尼亞[[魯阿哈國家公園|魯阿哈]]和[[卡塔維國家公園|卡塔維國家公園]]的大象、水牛以及獅子。其中一台還因獅子的襲擊而被毀。<ref>{{cite web | author=National Geographic Society | title=Lion Steals Roving Camera, Takes Photos | date=April 27, 2010 | url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/04/photogalleries/100427-lion-steals-camera-remote-science-pictures/ | accessdate=2013-09-19 | archive-date=2013-09-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921090958/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/04/photogalleries/100427-lion-steals-camera-remote-science-pictures/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>

二人在2011年又出產了兩台BeetleCams，以拍攝獅子的影像。<ref>{{cite web |author = Paul Marks, New Scientist |title = Safari robot snaps feasting lion up close |date = 9 March 2012 |url = http://www.newscientist.com/blogs/shortsharpscience/2012/03/safari-robot-captures-breakfas.html |accessdate = 2013-09-19 |archive-date = 2013-09-21 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053431/http://www.newscientist.com/blogs/shortsharpscience/2012/03/safari-robot-captures-breakfas.html |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author = Will Burrard-Lucas |title = BeetleCam vs the Lions of the Masai Mara |date = 29 Feb 2012 |url = http://blog.burrard-lucas.com/2012/02/beetlecam-lions-masai-mara/ |accessdate = 2013-09-19 |archive-date = 2012-03-10 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120310131440/http://blog.burrard-lucas.com/2012/02/beetlecam-lions-masai-mara/ |dead-url = no }}</ref> BeetleCam Mark II 使用[[佳能EOS系列|Canon EOS]] 1Ds Mk III。<ref>{{cite web|author = The Telegraph|title = Camouflaged camera films lions close up in Kenya's Masai Mara|date = 1 Mar 2012|url = http://www.telegraph.co.uk/earth/earthvideo/9115732/Camouflaged-camera-films-lions-close-up-in-Kenyas-Masai-Mara.html|accessdate = 2013-09-19|archive-date = 2013-09-21|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130921122858/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/earth/earthvideo/9115732/Camouflaged-camera-films-lions-close-up-in-Kenyas-Masai-Mara.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>

